text: Ray Peat was talking about how with prolonged high thyroid supplementation some women he knew were able to shrink their ovarian cysts, "Fluid filled capsules anywhere in the body respond to hypothyroidism by swelling, and they shrink in the presence of increased thyroid hormone."

When a cell is exposed to estrogen, the first thing it does is take up more water, estrogen is a regulator of water and osmolarity. So I think there is a correlation between how cells and cysts, capsules, etc. respond to various hormones. Because I guess cells are fluid sacs too.

I wonder with continued discussion about "China vs. America" when will people rediscover that Jack London wrote a story about Americans genociding China using bioweapons. I have heard that Hirohito read it and was so horrified he set it as his goal to protect Asia from the USA.

This was from an era where science fiction informed operational planning. I think a lot of the details like the plague being chosen as the agent for the attack are not coincidental and its publishing was probably taken as a major provocation.
